<sect1 id="libglvnd" xreflabel="libglvnd-&libglvnd-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="libglvnd.html"?>

  <title>libglvnd-&libglvnd-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="libglvnd">
    <primary sortas="a-glvnd">libglvnd</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to libglvnd</title>

    <para>
      libglvnd is a vendor-neutral dispatch layer for arbitrating
      OpenGL API calls between multiple vendors. It allows multiple
      drivers from different vendors to coexist on the same filesystem,
      and determines which vendor to dispatch each API call to at
      runtime.
    </para>

    <para>
      In other words, this package contains OpenGL libraries and wrappers.
      <xref linkend="mesa"/> also provides OpenGL libraries. You will need to
      decide which provider you want to install from. This package is
      required by <xref linkend="nvidia"/> as that driver will not be able to
      use <application>Mesa's</application> OpenGL libraries; however, every
      other driver, including those in <application>Mesa</application>, can
      simply use its OpenGL libraries. Furthermore, no programs in this book
      require this package. Problems may arise with some build systems
      expecting certain files or binary-downloaded applications such as <ulink
      url="https://www.shipofharkinian.com/">Ship of Harkinian</ulink> being
      linked against this package's libraries which are not provided by <xref
      linkend="mesa"/>, though these issues are few and far between.
    </para>

    <para>
      It is up to you on which provider to install from. If you don't want to
      install OpenGL libraries from this package, you can skip this page and
      continue onto the next package. If you want to install this package, but
      not <xref linkend="nvidia"/>, you will still need to install <xref
      linkend="mesa"/>. Its instructions will account for this installation.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&libglvnd-download-https;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (FTP): <ulink url="&libglvnd-download-ftp;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

